question: How do I perform a factory reset on my Samsung phone?
answer: To factory reset your Samsung phone: 1. Go to Settings > General Management > Reset > Factory Reset. 2. Tap "Reset Device". 3. Enter your PIN/pattern if prompted. 4. Tap "Delete All". Warning: This will erase all data.
follow_up: Would you like to know how to backup your data before performing a factory reset?

question: Why is my Samsung phone battery draining so quickly?
answer: Quick battery drain can be caused by: 1. Background apps 2. High screen brightness 3. Location services 4. Poor network connection. Check battery usage in Settings > Battery to identify power-hungry apps.
follow_up: Would you like to learn about power-saving modes?

question: How do I update my Samsung phone software?
answer: To update your phone: 1. Go to Settings > Software Update 2. Tap "Download and Install" 3. If an update is available, follow the prompts to install it. Ensure your phone is charged and connected to Wi-Fi.
follow_up: Would you like to enable automatic updates?

question: How do I connect my Samsung tablet to Wi-Fi?
answer: To connect to Wi-Fi: 1. Go to Settings > Connections > Wi-Fi 2. Turn on Wi-Fi 3. Select your network 4. Enter password if required. Your tablet will remember the network for future use.
follow_up: Would you like to learn about managing saved Wi-Fi networks?

question: How do I adjust the temperature in my Samsung refrigerator?
answer: To adjust temperature: 1. Locate the control panel 2. Press the Fridge or Freezer button 3. Use arrows to set desired temperature 4. Wait 24 hours for temperature to stabilize.
